                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <locus from="2r" to="44vb"/> and <locus from="55vb" to="57vb"/>
                        <seg type="script">Eighteenth-century script.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (strong red).</seg>
                        <desc>Good, slightly careless and uneven hand; slenderer than <ref type="hand" target="#h2">Hand 2</ref>.</desc>
                        
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ማርያ፡</abbr> for <expan>ማርያም፡</expan> (<locus target="#24vc #148rb"/>)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ፍካ፡</abbr> for <expan>ፍካሬ፡</expan> (<locus target="#143va"/>)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ክፍ፡</abbr> for <expan>ክፍል፡</expan> (<locus target="#149va #155ra"/>)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ትእዛ፡</abbr> for <expan>ትእዛዝ፡</expan> (<locus target="#154rc"/>)</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Divine names; a few lines in the incipit page, alternating with black lines; 
                           two initial lines of each subsection of the text; elements of punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals; some words like <foreign xml:lang="gez">fǝkkāre</foreign>
                           (e.g., <locus target="#142vc #143ra #143va"/>), <foreign xml:lang="gez">kǝfl</foreign> (e.g., <locus target="#147vb #148vc #149ra"/>), 
                           <foreign xml:lang="gez">tǝʾǝzaz </foreign>(e.g., <locus target="#154rc #154vc"/>), <foreign xml:lang="gez">rabʿ</foreign> (<locus target="#154rc"/>), etc.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">
                     <locus from="44vb" to="55vb"/>
                        <seg type="script">Eighteenth-century script.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (strong red).</seg>
                        <desc>Good, slightly careless and uneven; broader and smaller than the <ref type="hand" target="#h1">main Hand 1</ref>.</desc>
                     </handNote>
                     
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus from="157vc" to="158rc"/>
                           <desc type="Letter">A letter from <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7830Petros"><t:roleName xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="function">Metropolitan</t:roleName>Ṗeṭros IV</persName> to the community of <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0105DD">Dabra Dāmmo</placeName>.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">መልእክት፡ ዘፈነዋ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት፡ ዘመንግሥተ፡ ኢትዮጵያ፡ ገብሩ፡ ወሐዋርያሁ፡ ለክርስቶስ፡ ወልዱ፡ ለቅዱስ፡ ማርቆስ፡ ወንጌላዊ፡ ትብጻሕ፡ ኀበ፡ <sic>ውሉዱየ</sic>፡ ፍቁራንየ፡ ቡሩካን፡ ወቅዱሳን፡ ማኅበረ፡ ደብረ፡ ዳሞ፡</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">A letter sent by Ṗeṭros, the metropolitan of the kingdom of Ethiopia, the servant and Apostle of Christ, the son of Saint Luke the Apostle, may it reach to my beloved children, the blessed and the holy community of Dabra Damo … </q>
                           <note>The introduction is written in Gǝʿǝz whereas the main body in Amharic. The letter was most likely written by <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7830Petros">Ṗeṭros IV</persName> who arrived in Ethiopia in <date>1881</date> during
                              the reign of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10378Yohanne">Yoḥannǝs IV</persName>. Another letter of the metropolitan is contained in the manuscript <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESqdgm003">Dagʿa Tamben, Qaqamā Dabra Gannat Qǝddǝst Māryām, QDGM-003</ref>.</note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <locus target="#2r"/>
                           <desc type="StampExlibris">Shelfmark C3-IV-266</desc></item>

                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <locus target="#1r"/>
                           <desc type="StampExlibris">Shelfmark 312</desc></item>
                        
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <locus target="#1r"/>
                           <desc>The title of the main text of the manuscript <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሃይማኖተ <supplied reason="omitted">፡</supplied> አበው</foreign></desc> 
                        </item>
                           <item xml:id="e4">
                           <locus target="#40rb"/>
                              <desc>The name of the original owner was erased and replaced by the name <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14727WaldaHeywat">Walda Ḥǝywat</persName>; written in a secondary hand.</desc></item>
                           
                        <item xml:id="e5">
                           <locus target="#157vb"/>
                           <desc>Final note, most probably concerning the donation of the manuscript, was erased.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e6">
                           <locus target="#18vc #19ra #113vb"/>
                           <desc> Corrections over erasures by the <ref type="hand" target="#h1">main Hand 1</ref>.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
